text: Beşbarmaq (; Uzbek: norin, нарын) is the national dish of Kyrgyzstan, Bashkortostan, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan. It is also the main course on feasts in Kyrgyzstan and Uzbekistan. It is made from meat, with chopped noodles and onion sauce. == sources == *https://www.ratgeber- rezepte.de/rezept-beshbarmak.shtml == References == Category:Kyrgyz food Category:Kazakh food Category:Uzbekistani food Category:Turkmen culture
title: Beşbarmaq
